## 1. Principles
- **Component library first, inline code never** (CODING_PHILOSOPHY Layer 3).
- **Semantic tokens over raw values** — never hard-code a color or spacing.
- **Accessible by default** — WCAG AA is the floor, not a feature.

## 2. Semantic tokens
_Define intent, not appearance. Map tokens → theme values in one place._

| Token | Purpose | Light | Dark |
|-------|---------|-------|------|
| `--color-bg` | Page background | `<hex>` | `<hex>` |
| `--color-surface` | Cards, panels | `<hex>` | `<hex>` |
| `--color-text` | Primary text | `<hex>` | `<hex>` |
| `--color-text-muted` | Secondary text | `<hex>` | `<hex>` |
| `--color-primary` | Primary action | `<hex>` | `<hex>` |
| `--color-danger` | Destructive | `<hex>` | `<hex>` |
| `--color-border` | Dividers | `<hex>` | `<hex>` |

## 3. Scales
- **Spacing:** `4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64` (px) — use the scale, never arbitrary values.
- **Radius:** `sm 4 · md 8 · lg 16 · full 9999`.
- **Type:** `xs 12 · sm 14 · base 16 · lg 18 · xl 24 · 2xl 32`. Line-height ≥ 1.4 for body.

## 4. Theme architecture
- Tokens defined on `:root`; dark theme via `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` **and**
  an explicit `[data-theme]` override that wins in both directions.
- Components read **only** tokens — never a raw hex or px literal.

## 5. Accessibility (WCAG AA)
- Text contrast ≥ **4.5:1** (≥ **3:1** large text & UI components).
- Full keyboard operability; visible focus rings.
- Labels on all inputs; `alt` on images; accessible names on icon buttons.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## 6. Component classes (BEM)
`block__element--modifier`, e.g. `card__title--featured`. Every interactive element gets a
semantic `id` and BEM class.

## 7. Anti-patterns (never do)
- ❌ Hard-coded colors/spacing instead of tokens.
- ❌ New inline component when a library one exists.
- ❌ Removing focus outlines without a visible replacement.
- ❌ Color as the only signal of state (add icon/text).
- ❌ Fixed pixel heights that clip content at larger font sizes.
